PANEL STRUCTURE & CAMERA LANGUAGE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Panel 1 – Side Profile Close-Up:
- Tight side-face close-up of the character
- Character is reading on the bed
- Facial features must match the talent reference exactly
- Shallow depth of field with soft background blur
- Preserve the cold-toned lighting and mood from the environment reference
- Focus on eyes, skin texture, and calm concentration

Panel 2 – Back View Reading:
- Recreate the “lying on the bed reading” posture from the environment reference
- Use the exact talent from the character reference
- Clothing must match the garment reference if provided
- Emphasize the snowy exterior visible through the window
- Maintain realistic indoor–outdoor light balance

Panel 3 – Medium Shot, Low Angle:
- Medium framing from a low, upward-looking angle
- Camera position creates visual tension and emphasizes the narrowness of the room
- Highlight spatial relationships between character, bookshelf, and poster-covered wall
- Strong sense of depth and confinement
- Physically correct perspective, no exaggeration

Panel 4 – Wide / Fisheye Establishing Shot:
- Wide-angle or fisheye-style perspective inspired by the environment reference
- Show the entire room layout
- Reinforce the “snowy day at home” atmosphere
- Maintain realistic distortion consistent with wide optics
- Establish spatial continuity with previous panels

